    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Tomato Vigil</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By PATRICIA JONAS</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Jonas, Patricia</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Now is time to inspect tomato plants for green tomato hornworms (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Inspect tomato plants closely for green tomato hornworms. These large caterpillars often go unnoticed until a plant is suddenly stripped of leaves. The best control is daily inspection and handpicking. Leave caterpillars that have puffy ricelike grains on their backs: these are the cocoons of beneficial wasps that parasitize hornworms.</p>
        <p>Don't harvest onions and shallots until the tops have flopped over.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Inspect tomato plants closely for green tomato hornworms. These large caterpillars often go unnoticed until a plant is suddenly stripped of leaves. The best control is daily inspection and handpicking. Leave caterpillars that have puffy ricelike grains on their backs: these are the cocoons of beneficial wasps that parasitize hornworms.</p>
        <p>Don't harvest onions and shallots until the tops have flopped over.</p>
        <p>Now through September is an ideal time to reseed lawns. Keep well watered until germination.</p>
        <p>PATRICIA JONAS</p>
        <p>CUTTINGS: THIS WEEK</p>
